<HEADLINE>
FT  03 SEP 94 / Finance and the Family: Smaller company shares improve  - At
a glance
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Smaller company share prices continued to improve this week. The Hoare
Govett Smaller Companies Index (capital gains version) climbed 0.4 per cent
to 1715.16 over the week to September 1. The index is up 1.4 per cent since
the start of the year, while the FT-SE-A All-Share is down 4.2 per cent over
the same period, and the FT-SE 100 is down 5.9 per cent.
</TEXT>
