<HEADLINE>
FT  03 SEP 94 / Finance and the Family: Tied or untied?  - At a glance
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Life insurance advice is still driven by commission and can be 'wholly
inappropriate' according to the Consumer's Association. Its monthly
publication, Which?, sent researchers to 30 financial advisers. Some were
independent, some tied - only able to recommend the products of one company
 -and others were based at banks or building societies. 'Too many advisers
recommended commission-generating products at the expense of appropriate
advice. IFAs were no better than tied agents,' concluded Which?
</TEXT>
