FT  03 SEP 94 / Chechen rebels head for capital
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOHN LLOYD and Agencies
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MOSCOW
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Opposition forces in the Russian North Caucasian republic of Chechnya are
moving closer to the capital, Grozny - and are calling for the overthrow of
the republic's president, General Dzhokar Dudayev. According to spokesmen
for the various forces now opposing Gen Dudayev, four regions are under
their control and highways to Grozny have been cut a few kilometres from the
city. The Chechen provisional council, the main opposition group, said that
