<HEADLINE>
FT  02 SEP 94 / World Stock Markets: Brazil rises 2 per cent
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Sao Paulo closed up 2.02 per cent in moderate trade boosted by a speculative
late rally in oil and mining shares.
The Bovespa index of the 56 most-active shares ended up 1,074 at 54,369
points. Volume was RDollars 366m (Dollars 414m).
Brokers said major players bought heavily in the cash market in the
afternoon to carry out speculative day-trade operations in the Bovespa
futures index market.
Prices were also bolstered by two new opinion polls showing Mr Fernando
Henrique Cardoso, the former economy minister, has improved his chances of
winning the presidential election outright in the first round of voting on
October 3.
Mexico
Equities closed down for the sixth successive session on the back of
widespread profit-taking with the market even falling below a key support
level.
The key IPC index closed off 9.12 points at 2,693.61 - a loss of 0.34 per
cent. At the end of 1993, the IPC stood at 2,602.63.
Volume totalled 801.9m new pesos, on 58.1m shares traded. The market has
lost 3.75 per cent in the last six sessions from a post-election high of
2,798 points on August 24.
