FT  02 SEP 94 / World Commodities Prices: Wool
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Prices at sales this week continued the rise which has characterised the
1994/95 selling season, with auctions resumed in all primary markets during
the past five weeks. There has also been good demand for Australian
stockpile wool, with disposals far exceeding the present monthly fixed
schedule. Buying interest stretches well forward, with inroads now being
made into the months from January onwards when stockpile sales will be twice
the present rate. The rising wool price trend is also bringing out steady
business in wool textile semi-manufactures, though there is considerable
price resistance and raw wool markets are showing more buoyancy than applies
further down the manufacturing line. The Australian Eastern states market
indicator ended the week at 739c/kg, compared with 728c/kg a week before.
